A BILL FORAN ACT
RELATING TO CIVIL IDENTIFICATION.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Section 286-303, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by amending subsection (c) to read as follows:
3 "(c) Every application for an identification card or
4 duplicate of an identification card shall be made on a form
5 developed by the director and furnished by the examiner of
6 drivers, signed by the applicant, and signed by the applicant's
7 parent or guardian if the applicant is under [eighteen] sixteen
8 years of age. The application shall contain the following
9 information:
10 (1) Name and complete address, including the number and
11 street name, of the applicant's permanent residence;
12 (2) The applicant's occupation and any pertinent data
13 relating thereto;
14 (3) The applicant's citizenship status;
15 (4) The applicant's veteran status if applicable and
16 desired by the applicant;
17 (5) The applicant's date and place of birth;
2026-3281 HB1667 GDI HMSO

Page 2 H.B. NO. 2^1
C.D. 1
1 (6) General description of the applicant, including the
2 applicant's gender designation, height, weight, hair
3 color, and eye color;
4 (7) The applicant's left and right index fingerprints or,
5 if clear impressions cannot be obtained, other
6 identifying imprints as specified by rules of the
7 director;
8 (8) The social security number of the applicant; and
9 (9) A digitized frontal photograph of the applicant's full
10 face.
11 Each applicant shall present documentary evidence as required by
12 the examiner of drivers of the applicant's age and identity, and
13 the applicant shall swear or affirm that all information given
14 is true and correct; provided that an applicant shall not be
15 required to provide documentation to prove the applicant's
16 gender designation other than the applicant's self-certification
17 of their chosen gender designation; provided further that
18 documentation that may incidentally show an applicant's birth
19 gender may be required if necessary to establish that the
20 applicant is legally entitled to an identification card.
